name: Marina Bay
description: Iconic waterfront promenade showcasing Singapore's modern skyline
notes: Best visited at sunset or night. Easy walking loop connects MBS and Gardens by the Bay.

name: Merlion Park
description: Home to Singapore's iconic half-lion half-fish statue
notes: Visit early morning to avoid crowds and get better photos.

name: Marina Bay Sands Mall
description: Luxury shopping mall featuring indoor canals and designer boutiques
notes: Connects seamlessly to ArtScience Museum and Spectra show area.

name: Singapore Flyer
description: Asia's largest observation wheel offering panoramic city views
notes: Full rotation takes ~30 minutes. Go near sunset for both day and night lighting.

name: ArtScience Museum
description: Museum featuring innovative digital art and immersive exhibitions
notes: Book tickets ahead on weekends. Combine visit with Marina Bay Sands area.

name: Gardens by the Bay
description: Futuristic park with climate-controlled conservatories and Supertree Grove
notes: Book timed entry online (Klook works fine). Allow 2-3 hours to explore fully.

name: Cloud Forest
description: Indoor biodome featuring world's tallest indoor waterfall and mountain landscape
notes: Perfect midday escape from heat. Bring a light jacket as it's air-conditioned.

name: Flower Dome
description: World's largest glass greenhouse with themed floral displays
notes: Purchase combo ticket with Cloud Forest for better value.

name: CHIJMES
description: Gothic-style former convent converted into dining and entertainment complex
notes: Great for evening drinks. Photogenic courtyard architecture.

name: Haji Lane
description: Narrow street lined with colorful murals and independent boutiques
notes: Best visited late afternoon. Combine with nearby Arab Street.

name: Chinatown
description: Historic district featuring traditional shophouses and cultural sites
notes: Evening is most lively. Area has many excellent dessert spots.

name: Spectra Light Show
description: Free outdoor water and light show at Marina Bay Sands
notes: Shows at 8pm/9pm (Sun-Thu) plus 10pm (Fri-Sat). Arrive 15 minutes early for good spots.

name: Garden Rhapsody
description: Free nightly light and music show at Supertree Grove
notes: Daily shows at 7:45pm & 8:45pm. Sit on grass for best experience. Show runs ~15 minutes.

name: Fort Siloso
description: Historic WWII fortress with interactive exhibits and coastal views
notes: Can be hot at midday - bring water. Skywalk offers excellent views of South China Sea.

name: Skyline Luge
description: Gravity-powered cart rides down scenic tracks with chairlift return
notes: Go near dusk for Night Luge experience. Multi-ride packages offer better value.

name: MegaZip
description: 450m zipline ride soaring over Siloso Beach jungle canopy
notes: Wear closed-toe shoes (required). Arrive early to minimize queue times.

name: Chinatown Complex
description: Singapore's largest hawker centre with over 260 food stalls
notes: Multiple MICHELIN-listed stalls. Visit for lunch or dinner.

name: Yat Ka Yan
description: Specialty dessert shop famous for durian chendol and traditional sweets
notes: Located in Bugis Fortune Centre. Best visited mid-afternoon.

name: Mei Heong Yuen
description: Traditional Chinatown dessert shop known for almond paste and peanut soup
notes: Located on Temple Street. Popular after-dinner spot.

name: ICE & TIME
description: Japanese-style kakigori shaved ice with creative toppings
notes: Located in Tanjong Pagar. Excellent post-dinner dessert option.

name: Old Amoy Chendol
description: Hawker stall serving artisanal coconut milk chendol with gula melaka
notes: Located in Chinatown Complex. Expect lines during peak lunch hours.

name: 75 Ah Balling
description: Peanut soup with handmade tang yuan (glutinous rice balls)
notes: Multiple outlets across Singapore. Flagship location at Golden Mile Complex.

name: Un Yang Kor Dai
description: Authentic northeastern Thai (Isaan) restaurant known for bold flavors
notes: Book ahead on weekends. Spice levels can be very intense - adjust to taste.

name: Ah Heng Curry Chicken
description: Hawker stall specializing in curry chicken served over bee hoon noodles
notes: MICHELIN Guide-listed hawker stall. Great value for money.

name: Mini Toast House
description: Old-school bakery selling traditional kaya buns and sweet toast
notes: Located in Chinatown Complex. Arrive early for best selection of fresh buns.

name: Shanghai Fried XLB
description: Hawker stall famous for xiao long bao with crispy pan-fried bottoms
notes: Located in Chinatown Complex. Look for stall signage inside the hawker centre.

name: Tai Weng Chicken Rice
description: Hainanese chicken rice with tender poached chicken and fragrant rice
notes: Located in Chinatown Complex. Reliable choice for lunch.

name: Delhi Lahori
description: Indian Muslim stall serving tandoor naan and grilled kebabs
notes: Located in Tekka Centre. Open long hours. Excellent value for authentic flavors.

name: Keng Eng Kee Seafood
description: MICHELIN-listed zi char restaurant famous for salted egg crab
notes: MICHELIN Guide recognition. Best visited with a group to share dishes family-style.
